name: Aui.Dropdown

types.name: Alignment
types.comment: Alignment relative to the button for the dropdown container.

types.name: Config
types.comment: Configuration type to show a dropdown component.

types.name: Msg
types.comment: Messages being sent by the dropdown component

values.name: baseConfig
values.comment:
Create a base configuration with a Msg mapping function.

    type Msg = DropdownMsg Aui.Dropdown.Msg

    dropdown (baseConfig DropdownMsg) ...

values.name: close
values.comment: Change a dropdown to a closed state. Convenient when you handle an action from an item in the dropdown in your own update function.

values.name: dropdown
values.comment:
Present a dropdown given a configuration, button content, dropdown content and a model.

    dropdown (baseConfig DropdownMsg |> withStyle Primary |> withAlignment Right)
        [ text "Open me"]
        [ dropdownSection (Just "Section Title")
            [ ul []
                [ li [] a [] [text "Item 1"]
                , li [] a [] [text "Item 2"]
                ]
            ]
        ]
        dropdownModel
values.type: Aui.Dropdown.Config a -> List (Html.Html Aui.Dropdown.Msg) -> List (Html.Html a) -> Aui.Dropdown.Model -> Html.Html a

values.name: dropdownSection
values.comment: Creates a section for within a dropdown container.
values.type: Maybe.Maybe String -> List (Html.Html a) -> Html.Html a

values.name: initialModel
values.comment: Default model for a dropdown component

values.name: leftAlignment
values.comment: Left alignment of the dropdown respectively to the button

values.name: open
values.comment: Change a dropdown to an opened state.

values.name: rightAlignment
values.comment: Right alignment of the dropdown respectively to the button

values.name: update
values.comment: Update function for the dropdown component. This should be called from within your update function when handling `Msg`

values.name: withAlignment
values.comment: Align the container for the dropdown to the side of the dropdown button.

values.name: withStyle
values.comment: Set the style of the dropdown button.

name: Aui.Toolbar

values.name: toolbar
values.comment:
Create a toolbar:

    toolbar
        [ toolbarPrimary
            [ buttonGroup [ button baseConfig Edit [ text "Edit" ] ]
            , buttonGroup
                [ button baseConfig Assign [ text "Assign" ]
                , button baseConfig AssignMe [ text "Assign to me" ]
                ]
            ]
        , toolbarSecondary [ button baseConfig Configure [ icon Small Configure ] ]
        ]

values.name: toolbarGroup
values.comment: Create toolbar button group

values.name: toolbarPrimary
values.comment: Create primary part of toolbar.

values.name: toolbarSecondary
values.comment: Create secondary part of toolbar.

name: Aui.Buttons

types.name: Config
types.comment: Configuration type for presenting a button.

types.name: Style
types.comment: Different styles available for a button.

values.name: baseConfig
values.comment: A configuration with sane defaults (no style, no anchor, enable, ect.).

values.name: button
values.comment:
Render an AUI button.

    button (baseConfig |> withStyle Primary |> withHref "http://elm-lang.org/")
        ButtonClicked
        [ text "Click me!"]
values.type: Aui.Buttons.Config a -> List (Html.Html a) -> Html.Html a

values.name: buttonGroup
values.comment:
Button container that will add the correct classes to make a button group.

    buttonGroup
        [ button config Clicked1 [text "First"]
        , button config Clicked2 [text "Second"]
        , button config Clicked3 [text "Third"]
        ]

values.name: disable
values.comment:
Add the disabled state to a button.

    baseConfig |> disable

values.name: forceAnchor
values.comment:
Forces the anchor tag to be used instead of the default button tag (only if no href is specified).

    baseConfig |> forceAnchor

values.name: withAction
values.comment:
Add an action to the buttons configuration.

    baseConfig |> withAction MyAction

values.name: withActive
values.comment:
Make a button active or not active.

    baseConfig |> withActive True

values.name: withAdditionalClass
values.comment:
Add additional classes to the button

    baseConfig |> additionalClass "my-button"

values.name: withHref
values.comment:
Add a href to the buttons configuration.

    baseConfig |> withHref "http://elm-lang.org/"

values.name: withStyle
values.comment:
Add a button style to the configuration.

    baseConfig |> withStyle Subtle
